Here's how you can do it:

1. First, create the following function in the view file, which checks if the byte array starts with a particular byte sequence:

```csharp
@functions {
    private bool ByteArrayStartsWith(byte[] array, params byte[] values)
    {
        if (array.Length < values.Length)
        {
            return false;
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < values.Length; i++)
        {
            if (array[i] != values[i])
            {
                return false;
            }
        }

        return true;
    }
}
```

2. Next, create a function to determine the content type based on the byte array:

```csharp
@functions {
    private string DetermineImageContentType(byte[] imgData)
    {
        if (imgData != null)
        {
            // Check for the PNG file header (89 50 4E 47 0D 0A 1A 0A)
            if (ByteArrayStartsWith(imgData, 0x89, 0x50, 0x4E, 0x47, 0x0D, 0x0A, 0x1A, 0x0A))
            {
                return "image/png";
            }
            // Check for the JPEG file header (FF D8)
            else if (ByteArrayStartsWith(imgData, 0xFF, 0xD8))
            {
                return "image/jpeg";
            }
        }

        return null;
    }
}
```

3. Finally, adjust your image rendering code to use the `DetermineImageContentType()` function:

```csharp
@foreach (var ad in ViewBag.AdsList as List<Ads>)
{
    byte[] imgData = null;

